transcript.text: Hello, welcome to On Print Shop.
In today's video we will walk you through the on Print Shop admin panel.
The admin panel is the interface that allows you to control and manage your store, starting with setting up your store for your users along with fulfilling the customer orders.
Now when you log into your admin panel, the first screen you see is your dashboard at the top left corner of the screen.
We have provided these five shortcuts for quick navigation.
Using these, you can navigate to the orders, customers, products, templates, and Site settings respective sections.
Let's move to the top center of the screen.
Here we have an admin search functionality where the admin can search for any menu, setting order, customer, product, etcetera from the search bar.
For more details on this functionality, you can go through the video from our help portal.
In the top right corner you can see the cache button which you can enable or disable and delete the cache memory from your admin panel.
From the blue down arrow icon, you can access the HTML help for setting up your front store.
Navigate to the solution help and find out the store's current version.
Next to this is the desktop icon.
Clicking on it will redirect you to the front retail store for asking your queries.
You can always use this live chat icon.
The notification icon allows you to see all the new notifications like orders, customers, etcetera.
The bell will always move whenever you receive any new notification.
In the corner you will find the profile drop down.
You can set Favorite links which allows you to set up icons and links in the left favorite section.
Also, you can anytime change your account password by using this button.
You will get the option to log out of your account.
In the below you can change the store details using the login as a filter or changing the store from the drop down menu.
Next to it, we have the option to maximize and minimize the current screen.

Moving towards the center of the screen, you can see these quick links at the top for orders, quotes, customers, products, templates, etcetera, on which you can click and go to the respective section.
Then in the dashboard, we have given admin data summaries like recent orders, sales statistics, sales orders, etcetera.
We have given a search box feature in some of the widgets and some of the widgets have a view all button for you to see all details in the respective section.
We also have a refresh button that loads the recent data.
In the sales order statistics.
We can see the stats of the last 12 months by default, but by clicking on this button, you can view the current month's details.
We have this wheel icon here for you to manage the hide and show of widgets in the dashboard.
To offer a unique user experience, we allowed our admins to manage the position of the widgets as per their preference with the drag and drop feature.
Moreover, in the left panel navigation, you will see and manage all the sections.
For how to manage these sections, you can anytime refer to our help portal in detail.
In the top left corner, you will be able to see the details of the account and store who is currently logged into the system.

For example, whenever any admin is logged in, it will display the admin and store name, or if some printer sales agent or B to B store is logged in, then it will display printer sales agent and B to B with their store names respectively.
Last but not least, you will be able to see bread Crumbs at this location with the links to go to the previous pages.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
